'''Lee Dong-gyeong''' ({{Ko-hhrm|이동경}}; born 20 September 1997) is a South Korean professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Ulsan HD FC|Ulsan HD]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=S. Korea football coach Bento sees versatility as strength for nat'l team |url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20190826004800315 |publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |date=26 August 2019 |access-date=26 August 2019 |archive-date=26 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190826114034/https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20190826004800315 |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Club career==
===Ulsan HD===
Prior to the 2018 season, Lee dropped out of [[Hongik University]] and joined [[K League 1]] club Ulsan Hyundai (renamed [[Ulsan HD FC|Ulsan HD]] in 2024). On 29 July 2018, he made his professional debut in a 1–1 draw with [[Jeju SK FC|Jeju United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.soccerway.com/match/jeju-sk-vFZJewv4/ulsan-hyundai-EVEwgyOM/summary/lineups/?mid=lQdbMc6j |title=
JEJ 1-1 ULS {{!}} Jeju SK v Ulsan HD live scores & match info |publisher=Soccerway |date=2018-07-29 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref> After making his first appearance at Ulsan, he was loaned to [[K League 2]] club [[FC Anyang]] for the second half of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kleague.com/news_view.do?seq=3087&orderBy=seq&viewOption=album&page=1 |script-title=ko:[안양] FC안양, 울산에서 MF 이동경 임대 영입 |language=ko |publisher=K League |date=2018-07-31 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref>

During the [[2019 K League 1|2019 season]], he found his spot at Ulsan, playing 25 K League 1 matches.<ref name="kleague"/> On 18 May 2019, Lee scored his first professional goal in a 3–1 win over [[Suwon Samsung Bluewings]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20190518047500007 |script-title=ko:'이동경·김수안 골맛' 울산, 수원 꺾고 선두 질주 |language=ko |publisher=Yonhap News Agency |date=2019-05-18 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref>

Before the start of the 2020 season, he considered moving to [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/report-vancouver-whitecaps-chasing-south-korea-international-lee-dong-gyeong |title=Report: Vancouver Whitecaps chasing South Korea international Lee Dong-gyeong |publisher=Major League Soccer |date=2020-02-18 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref> but decided to stay at Ulsan to prepare for the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2020 Summer Olympics]] held in [[Japan]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.khan.co.kr/article/202003130930023 |script-title=ko:이동경이 밴쿠버 대신 잔류한 이유 "울산이 더 유럽에 가깝더라" |language=ko |publisher=Kyunghyang |date=2020-03-13 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref> However, manager [[Kim Do-hoon]] did not use him as a main player, and so he tried to negotiate with [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] in September.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/artigo/ulsan-hyundai-confirma-negociacoes-com-o-boavista-por-medio-sul-coreano/12768052 |title=Ulsan Hyundai confirma negociações com o Boavista por médio sul-coreano |language=pt |publisher=O Jogo |date=2020-09-28 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref> He already said goodbye to his teammates,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/kr/%EB%89%B4%EC%8A%A4/goal-live-%EB%AA%85%EB%8B%A8%EC%A0%9C%EC%99%B8-%EB%90%98%EC%97%88%EB%8D%98-%EC%9D%B4%EB%8F%99%EA%B2%BD-%EA%B9%80%EB%8F%84%ED%9B%88-%EC%9C%A0%EB%9F%BD-%EA%B0%84%EB%8B%A4-%EB%A7%88%EC%A7%80%EB%A7%89-%EC%A0%88%EC%B0%A8-%ED%95%84%EC%9A%94/tqcjtl9k2ikn1ozgrz4xgs2f6 |script-title=ko:[GOAL LIVE] 명단제외 되었던 이동경... 김도훈 "유럽 간다. 마지막 절차 필요" |language=ko |publisher=Goal |date=2020-10-02 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref> but the transfer was not realised due to a conflict about his agent's commission.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://m.sports.naver.com/kfootball/article/109/0004284362 |script-title=ko:이동경, 포르투갈 보아비스타 진출 무산... 울산 복귀 [단독] |language=ko |publisher=Osen |website=Naver |date=2020-10-05 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.donga.com/sports/article/all/20201012/103374217/1 |script-title=ko:자존심 지킨 형님, '벤투호'가 더 강했다…'김학범호' 월반 이동경의 비수 |language=ko |publisher=Sports Donga |date=2020-10-13 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref> He was able to regain his spot after manager Kim left the club the next year.<ref name="kleague"/>

====Loan to Schalke 04====
On 31 January 2022, Lee joined [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] on loan until the end of the season, with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite press release |publisher=[[FC Schalke 04]] |url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/dong-gyeong-lee-join-fc-schalke-04-loan/ |title=Dong-gyeong Lee to join FC Schalke 04 on loan |date=31 January 2022 |access-date=7 February 2022 |archive-date=31 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220131231932/https://schalke04.de/en/team/dong-gyeong-lee-join-fc-schalke-04-loan/ |url-status=live}}</ref> On 13 February, he made his Schalke debut as a 60th-minute substitute in a 2–1 defeat to [[Fortuna Düsseldorf]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/commentary/_/gameId/608960 |title=F Düsseldorf 2-1 Schalke (13 Feb, 2022) Final Score |publisher=ESPN |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref> After his first match, he injured his [[metatarsal bones]], not being able to play any more matches for the club.<ref name="bild">{{cite news |url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/hansa-rostock/hansa-rostocks-koreaner-darum-kommt-lee-nicht-in-fahrt-82668114.bild.html |title=Darum kommt Lee nicht in Fahrt |language=de |publisher=Bild |date=2023-01-24 |access-date=2025-12-21}}</ref> Schalke extended the loan deal until the end of 2022 in the summer,<ref>{{cite press release |publisher=[[FC Schalke 04]] |url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/fc-schalke-04-renew-dong-gyeong-lee-loan/ |title=FC Schalke 04 renew Dong-gyeong Lee loan |date=10 June 2022 |access-date=13 June 2022 |archive-date=10 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220610115414/https://schalke04.de/en/team/fc-schalke-04-renew-dong-gyeong-lee-loan/ |url-status=live}}</ref> but excluded him from their matches at the beginning of the next season despite his recovery.

====Loan to Hansa Rostock====
On 1 September, Lee was loaned to 2. Bundesliga club [[FC Hansa Rostock|Hansa Rostock]] after terminating the contract with Schalke early.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/dong-gyeong-lee-leaves-fc-schalke-04/ |title=Dong-gyeong Lee leaves FC Schalke 04 |publisher=FC Schalke 04 |date=1 September 2022 |access-date=5 September 2022 |archive-date=1 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220901165715/https://schalke04.de/en/team/dong-gyeong-lee-leaves-fc-schalke-04/ |url-status=live}}</ref> During the [[2022–23 2. Bundesliga|2022–23 season]], he usually played as a substitute for Rostock, making 12 appearances including two starts at the 2. Bundesliga.<ref name="wf"/> In the middle of the season, manager [[Patrick Glöckner]] pointed out Lee's physical weakness, and demanded to increase workrate and intensity of tussles from him.<ref name="bild"/>

====Enlistment in Gimcheon Sangmu====
In June 2024, Lee enlisted in [[Gimcheon Sangmu FC|Gimcheon Sangmu]], the military football club of the K League 1, after [[military recruit training]] for four weeks. He had seven goals and five assists in eight league matches during March and April before enlistment, but lost momentum due to the four-week training. Despite this, he reached double-digit goals in a season for the first time.<ref name="kleague"/>

In the [[2025 K League 1|2025 season]], Lee had 13 goals and 11 assists in 34 matches,<ref name="kleague"/> while leading Gimcheon to finish third at the K League 1. He received the [[K League Most Valuable Player Award]] at the end of the season.<ref name="mvp"/>

